Global Funds Buy Net 22.9 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-04-01T04:05:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/global-funds-buy-net-22-9-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 22.9
billion rupees ($513.6 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, declined 29.3 percent to 792.5 billion rupees, or
38.8 percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds bought a net 33.2 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
